Los Angeles-based Hyperkin has designed a case that adds the iconic directional arrows from the Nintendo Game Boy to an iPhone . 
  Called Smart Boy lets gamers play their existing Game Boy and Game Boy Color games cartridges on their Apple handset . 
  It was originally an April Fool's joke, but demand was so high the firm has announced plans to sell it . 
  The case was created by independent video game hardware developers Hyperkin . 
 